        <page n="04" image="pa.fr.vs.1861.12.04.04">
            <div type="a">
                <column>1</column>
                <head>President Davis's Message</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Criticizes the points made in Davis's message, particularly his rationale
                    for invading Kentucky and his attempt to arouse England against the United
                    States over the Mason and Slidell affair.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>3</column>
                <head>Putting Down the Screws</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt>"Must persecuting rampant Abolitionism be permitted to interfere with the
                    private business of men, and must we hereafter deal with those only who agree
                    with us in politics?"</excerpt>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Complains that the Republicans are encouraging their partisans to withdraw
                    their patronage from Democratic papers. The Spirit asserts that there is more to
                    a newspaper than merely politics and consequently these concerns should not
                    dissuade subscribers and advertisers.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <div type="l">
                <column>4</column>
                <head>Interesting Letter</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Letter from a Union soldier in South Carolina who claims Chambersburg as
                    his home town. In the letter, he describes life in the war.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look>x</look>
            </div>
            <pageNote/>
        </page>
        <page n="05" image="pa.fr.vs.1861.12.04.05">
